doc.after: Android is developed in private by Google until the latest changes and updates are ready to be released, at which point the source code is made available publicly.[91] This source code will only run without modification on select devices, usually the Nexus series of devices. The source code is, in turn, adapted by OEMs to run on their hardware.[92] Android's source code does not contain the often proprietary device drivers that are needed for certain hardware components.[93]
